The '''Q2 hold-out blaster pistol''' was a [[Blaster/Legends|blaster]] manufactured by [[Merr-Sonn Munitions, Inc./Legends|Merr-Sonn Munitions, Inc.]] during the time of the [[Galactic Republic/Legends|Galactic Republic]]. It was based on [[SoroSuub Corporation/Legends|SoroSuub Corporation's]] ELG line of Diplomat's Blasters, a line that includes the [[ELG-3A blaster pistol/Legends|ELG-3A blaster pistol]].

==Description==
[[File:Republic_Blaster.jpg|thumb|left|Q2 hold-out blaster pistol]]

Small enough to be concealed in the hand of a [[Human/Legends|Human]], the Q2 [[Hold-out blaster/Legends|hold-out blaster]] was common among undercover agents and those beings wishing to use a low-profile weapon. Due to its size, many systems declared this [[Blaster pistol/Legends|blaster pistol]] illegal, while others had its usage closely regulated. Other star systems tended to view it as a "self-defense" alternative to the other, more powerful personal [[Blaster/Legends|blaster]].

The Q2 was actually taller than it is long, being only 9.6 cm in length and 10.3 cm in height&mdash;from the bottom of the handle to the top of the receiver. A specialized [[Power cell/Legends|power pack]] was required, and could be purchased from any authorized Merr-Sonn dealer for twenty [[Galactic Credit Standard/Legends|credits]]. This supplied enough energy for six shots.<ref name="AEG" /> Unlike most handheld blaster weapons, the Q2 fired green blaster bolts, similar to the [[S-5 Security-grade blaster/ascension gun|S-5 heavy blaster pistol]].

==History==
{{Quote|Lady Valarian wants all of her new recruits to use these fresh Republic Blasters. So here you go. Be careful with it...|[[Ind]], to a spacer|<ref name="SWG:I" />}}
[[Queen/Legends|Queen]] [[Padmé Amidala/Legends|Padmé Amidala]] and her retinue of [[Handmaiden/Legends|handmaidens]] were trained to proficiency with these weapons.<ref name="NEGWT">''[[The New Essential Guide to Weapons and Technology]]''</ref> As it was believed that the Queen should have a last line of defense in case of attack, there was a cache of these blasters kept hidden in a secret compartment in the armrest of her [[Throne/Legends|throne]].<ref name="SWI TPM" /> When attacked by [[Bounty hunter/Legends|bounty hunters]] [[Chata Hyoki/Legends|Chata Hyoki]] and [[Robonino/Legends|Robonino]], [[Senator/Legends|Senator]] Padmé Amidala unsuccessfully attempted to subdue them with a Q2.<ref name="Pursuit of Peace">{{TCW|Pursuit of Peace}}</ref>

It was later used by the [[Smuggler/Legends|smuggler]] [[Dash Rendar/Legends|Dash Rendar]] as a last resort defending [[holostar]] [[Javul Charn]] from an attack from the [[Anomid/Legends|Anomid]] [[Assassin/Legends|assassin]], [[Edge (Anomid)|Edge]].<ref name="Shadow Games">''[[Shadow Games]]''</ref> During the [[Galactic Civil War/Legends|Galactic Civil War]], the [[Valarian Syndicate|Valarian criminal syndicate]] acquired a stock of Q2 blaster. [[Lady/Legends|Lady]] [[Valarian/Legends|Valarian's]] lieutenant [[Ind]] provided her new recruits with this weapon.<ref name="SWG:I" />

